Regenerating conifers are abundant throughout the whole area of deep bog peat that was previously planted, mostly 1-3 m tall. There are also some lines of taller conifers. These should all be felled and the brash removed. There is much brash present as a remnant from the earlier clear-felling operation which should have been removed in order to help the bog vegetation to recover.
